{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0411-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"48111"},"text":"§ 48111.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Funding proposals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0412-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Introduction in the Senate","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Within 15 days (not counting any day on which the Senate is not in session) after a funding proposal is submitted to the Senate by the Secretary of Transportation under section 274(c) of the Air Traffic Management System Performance Improvement Act of 1996, an implementing bill with respect to such funding proposal shall be introduced in the Senate by the majority leader of the Senate, for himself and the minority leader of the Senate, or by Members of the Senate designated by the majority leader and minority leader of the Senate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0413-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Consideration in the Senate","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"An implementing bill introduced in the Senate under subsection (a) shall be referred to the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation. The Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation shall report the bill with its recommendations within 60 days following the date of introduction of the bill. Upon the reporting of the bill by the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation, the reported bill shall be referred sequentially to the Committee on Finance for a period of 60 legislative days.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0414-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0415-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Implementing bill","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “implementing bill” means only a bill of the Senate which is introduced as provided in subsection (a) with respect to one or more Federal Aviation Administration funding proposals which contain changes in existing laws or new statutory authority required to implement such funding proposal or proposals.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0416-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Funding proposal","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “funding proposal” means a proposal to provide interim or permanent funding for operations of the Federal Aviation Administration.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0417-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Rules of the Senate","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of this section are enacted—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0418-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as an exercise of the rulemaking power of the Senate and as such they are deemed a part of the rules of the Senate and they supersede other rules only to the extent that they are inconsistent therewith; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e0419-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s48111/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" with full recognition of the constitutional right of the Senate to change the rules (so far as relating to the procedure of the Senate) at any time, in the same manner and to the same extent as in the case of any other rule of the Senate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcc6e041a-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/tII/s275/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–264, title II, § 275(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3246"},"text":"110 Stat. 3246","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcc6e041b-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcc6e041c-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcc6e041d-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 274(c) of the Air Traffic Management System Performance Improvement Act of 1996, referred to in subsec. (a), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/s274/c"},"text":"section 274(c) of Pub. L. 104–264","children":[],"tail":", which is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s40101"},"text":"section 40101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcc6e041e-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idcc6e041f-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective on date that is 30 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 1996","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/s203"},"text":"section 203 of Pub. L. 104–264","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date of 1996 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s106"},"text":"section 106 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Except as otherwise specifically provided, section applicable only to fiscal years beginning after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1996","children":[],"tail":", and not to be construed as affecting funds made available for a fiscal year ending before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1996","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 104–264","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date of 1996 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s106"},"text":"section 106 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
